@miltimore79 @RBReich My back-of-the-envelope calculation is that we spent about $30 trillion on entitlements (Social Security, Medicare, Medicaid, and others) over the same period.

A lot of that, obviously, has ended up in our national debt.

And … we can’t even tell the difference.

@SharylAttkisson Our govt's Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services says in 2019 14.9%  of Medicaid payments were improper representing $57.36B and 7.5% of Medicare payments were improper, representing $46.25B.

